# Copilot instructions for Finagler Full Semantic Refactor
# Source of truth: src/base.css

Objective:
Refactor all JSX/TSX files in the Finagler project to use semantic classNames
defined in src/base.css instead of Tailwind utilities or inline style objects.

Scope:
- Convert ALL Tailwind utility classNames (bg-*, p-*, m-*, text-*, flex, gap-*,
  items-*, justify-*, border-*, rounded-*, shadow-*, etc.)
- Convert ALL inline style={{…}} props to equivalent semantic classNames.
- Remove remaining inline style props entirely.
- Skip backend, schema, bridge, or config code (UI components only).

Allowed Vocabulary (defined in base.css):
panel, sidebar, toolbar, button, field, list, list-item,
text-muted, text-accent, warning, selected,
flex, column, row, center, flex-between, flex-gap,
gap-sm, gap-md, pad-sm, pad-md,
text-sm, text-md, text-lg, font-bold, font-light,
rounded, w-full, h-full, mr-sm, mr-md, scroll, scroll-area,
clickable, app-container, app-body, main-content, center-content, center-content-column,
table, loading-text, error-text, error-detail, fade-transition, fade-in, fade-out

Guidelines:
- Combine classes logically: e.g. className="panel flex column gap-md"
- Maintain all JSX structure and functional behavior exactly.
- Do NOT invent new or one-off classNames.
- Map inline style values to the closest semantic class (e.g. marginRight: '8px' → mr-md).
- If a color or background style (e.g. '#00B97A', '#d97706') is present,
  remove it and rely on domain CSS variables (--accent, --fg, --bg).
- Preserve all React logic, state, and hooks.

Special Rules:
- Dynamic inline styles using computed values (e.g. width: dynamicWidth) may remain inline.
- When multiple style props map to the same concept (e.g. padding + gap),
  use a single semantic equivalent if it matches intent.
- All text/font spacing or weight should map to text-sm/text-md/text-lg or font-bold/font-light.

Verification:
After each batch, run `npm run dev` to confirm visuals and interactivity are unchanged.
Domain theme switching should still affect colors and accents correctly.

Notes:
src/base.css defines the canonical design vocabulary.
If future helper classes are added there, Copilot may use them automatically.
Never modify base.css automatically — all new helpers must be added manually.
